President Trump made remarks in the Oval Office congratulating the leaders of Israel and Sudan for agreeing to normalize relations. He highlighted the historic significance of the peace agreement and emphasized the potential for trade, tourism, and cooperation between the two countries. The President also mentioned that there are other countries interested in joining similar agreements and that he believes Iran could potentially be involved in a future peace deal. He briefly discussed the ongoing stimulus talks with Speaker Pelosi and expressed his willingness to make a deal if the right compromises can be reached. The President also mentioned the conflict between Armenia and Azerbaijan and stated that progress is being made in addressing the issue.